Annotation Type ParamBinding

public @interface ParamBinding
Defines a single URI template parameter binding.
Author:
Alexander Rashed

  • Required Element Summary

    Required Elements
    Modifier and Type
    Required Element
    Description
    String
    name
    Name of the URI template parameter.
    String
    value
    Expression language expression specifying the value of the parameter.

  • Element Details

    • name

      String name
      Name of the URI template parameter.

    • value

      String value

      Expression language expression specifying the value of the parameter. These can be normal constant string values or EL expressions (${foo.bar}) that will resolve using either the default EL context, or the context specified by a @LinkELProvider annotation. The default context resolves any non-qualified variable to properties of the response entity for whom we're discovering links, and has an extra binding for the "this" variable which is the response entity as well.
